<div class="help-section">
    <nav class="help-breadcrumb"><a href="/help">Help</a> / <span>Accounts</span></nav>
    <h1><i class="fas fa-wallet"></i> Accounts (Funds)</h1>
    <p class="help-intro">Manage restricted and unrestricted funds.</p>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>What are Accounts?</h2>
        <p>Accounts (also called Funds) represent pools of money designated for specific purposes. This is a key concept in nonprofit fund accounting.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Account Types</h2>
        <table class="help-table">
            <tr><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Unrestricted</strong></td><td>Can be used for any purpose</td><td>General Operating Fund</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Temporarily Restricted</strong></td><td>Restricted by time or purpose, will become unrestricted</td><td>2024 Training Fund</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Permanently Restricted</strong></td><td>Principal must be maintained, only earnings can be used</td><td>Endowment Fund</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Restricted</strong></td><td>Donor-designated for specific purpose</td><td>Building Fund</td></tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Common Fire Department Accounts</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>General Fund</strong> - Day-to-day operations (Unrestricted)</li>
            <li><strong>Equipment Fund</strong> - Apparatus and gear purchases (Restricted)</li>
            <li><strong>Building Fund</strong> - Station improvements (Restricted)</li>
            <li><strong>Training Fund</strong> - Firefighter training (Temp. Restricted)</li>
            <li><strong>Memorial Fund</strong> - Fallen firefighter memorials (Restricted)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-warning">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
        <strong>Important:</strong> Restricted funds must only be used for their designated purpose. Misuse is a compliance violation.
    </div>
</div>
